India Sugar Production to Climb Next Year, USDA Unit Says

-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 
2011-04-20T19:16:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/india-sugar-production-to-climb-next-year-usda-unit-says.html
Sugar production in  India  will
climb to 28.3 million metric tons in the year that begins in
October, from an estimated 26.65 million tons in the previous 12
months, according to a unit of the U.S. Department of
Agriculture.  The Foreign Agricultural Service  report  was dated April 15
and posted today on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Campbell in Chicago at 
 ecampbell14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net . 